description:
&lt;p&gt;Within in Children and Young people Services in NHFT we are currently seeking to recruit a dedicated, compassionate &amp; motivated Specialist Paediatric Nurse. This is a new and exciting post based in the 0-19 team, but spanning across Children’s Specialist services, to assist with developing new ways of working and improving quality of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using advanced clinical skills, the Specialist Paediatric Nurse will have a countywide role with responsibility for providing expert knowledge to support the wider children’s workforce to meet the needs of children, young people and families where there are undifferentiated and undiagnosed developmental and behavioural presentations. The post holder will work independently, and alongside wider workforce, to develop pathways to ensure children receive high quality care by the right person, at the right time in the right place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is full time and initially for a 1 year fixed term period. Secondment will be considered for internal applicants. For more information about this post please contact Rachel Andrews, Public Health Matron, on 07718705499. The proposed interview date for candidates successful through the shortlisting process is November 26th 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Rachel Andrews&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Public Health Matron&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address rachel.andrews@nhft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 07718705499&lt;/p&gt;
